Software Requirements for FINAL_MAJOR_PROJECT
================================================

1. Overview
-----------
This document details the software requirements for the FINAL_MAJOR_PROJECT, covering all major components: AI Service (Python), Backend Server (Node.js), and Client Frontend (React + Vite).

2. AI Service (Python)
----------------------
**Location:** major_project1/ai-service/

**Requirements:**
- Python 3.x
- pip (Python package manager)

**Python dependencies (requirements.txt):**
- fastapi==0.104.1
- uvicorn==0.24.0
- pydantic==2.5.0
- scikit-learn==1.3.2
- numpy==1.24.3
- pandas==2.1.3

3. Backend Server (Node.js)
---------------------------
**Location:** major_project1/server/

**Requirements:**
- Node.js (Recommended: version ≥16.x, minimum 14.13.0)
- npm (Node package manager)

**npm dependencies (package.json):**
- axios (^1.6.2)
- bcryptjs (^2.4.3)
- cors (^2.8.5)
- dotenv (^16.3.1)
- express (^4.18.2)
- jsonwebtoken (^9.0.2)
- mongoose (^8.0.3)
- multer (^1.4.5-lts.1)
- nodemailer (^8.0.1)
- socket.io (^4.6.1)
- twilio (^4.20.0)

**Development dependencies:**
- nodemon (^3.0.2)

4. Client Frontend (React + Vite)
----------------------------------
**Location:** major_project1/client/

**Requirements:**
- Node.js (Recommended: version ≥16.x)
- npm

**npm dependencies (package.json):**
- react (^18.2.0)
- react-dom (^18.2.0)
- react-router-dom (^6.20.0)
- axios (^1.6.2)
- socket.io-client (^4.6.1)
- mapbox-gl (^3.0.1)
- recharts (^2.10.3)
- jspdf (^2.5.1)
- react-hot-toast (^2.4.1)

**Development dependencies:**
- @types/react (^18.2.43)
- @types/react-dom (^18.2.17)
- @vitejs/plugin-react (^4.2.1)
- autoprefixer (^10.4.16)
- postcss (^8.4.32)
- tailwindcss (^3.3.6)
- vite (^5.0.8)

5. General Requirements
----------------------
- Git (for version control)
- Code Editor (e.g., Visual Studio Code)
- Web Browser (for running/testing frontend)

6. Setup Instructions
---------------------

1. Install Node.js (≥16.x) and npm:
   Download Node.js: https://nodejs.org/

2. Install Python 3.x:
   Download Python: https://www.python.org/

3. Install Node.js dependencies:
   From major_project1/ root:
   npm run install-all

4. Set up the AI Python environment:
   From major_project1/ root:
   npm run install-ai
   This creates a virtual environment and installs Python dependencies.

5. Start the project:
   npm start
   This command runs the server, client, and AI service together if configured.

